SIMPLE: bubbler
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bubbler
<hw>Bub"bler</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cheat; to deceive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She has <qex>bubbled</qex> him out of his youth.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The great Locke, who was seldom outwitted by false sounds, was
nevertheless <qex>bubbled</qex> here.</q>
<rj><qau>Sterne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bubbler</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Bubbler
<hw>Bub"bler</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
cheats.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the Jews, jobbers, <qex>bubblers</qex>, subscribers,
projectors, etc.</q> <rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A fish of the Ohio river; -- so
called from the noise it makes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bubble shell</ent>⟦br⟧
